instead of pomegranates.

615
00:38:17,460 --> 00:38:19,380
Take your time, be patient.

616
00:38:27,700 --> 00:38:28,460
Where have you been?

617
00:38:28,620 --> 00:38:29,540
I've packed the stuff.

618
00:38:29,660 --> 00:38:30,580
We can go home anytime.

619
00:38:36,020 --> 00:38:37,100
Pomegranates?

620
00:38:37,260 --> 00:38:38,460
There's a pomegranate vendor here?

621
00:38:38,940 --> 00:38:40,100
I came across someone selling it.

622
00:38:46,060 --> 00:38:47,300
I've loved pomegranates since I was a kid.

623
00:38:47,700 --> 00:38:49,260
Just that they are too troublesome to peel.

624
00:38:55,380 --> 00:38:55,780
That's right.

625
00:38:56,260 --> 00:38:57,060
Did you bring back all the stuff

626
00:38:57,220 --> 00:38:58,180
from Bremen?

627
00:38:58,900 --> 00:38:59,740
Yes.

628
00:39:00,180 --> 00:39:00,860
Where did you send it to?

629
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:03,420
Your house or mine?

630
00:39:03,700 --> 00:39:05,140
The institute's dormitory.

631
00:39:08,420 --> 00:39:09,500
The bachelor apartment?

632
00:39:11,060 --> 00:39:12,940
You're occupying a bachelor's apartment as a married man.

633
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:14,580
Is the institute fine with that?

634
00:39:16,820 --> 00:39:17,740
You're already married.

635
00:39:17,900 --> 00:39:19,340
It's not a good idea to take up their place, right?

636
00:39:23,460 --> 00:39:24,860
When the luggage is delivered to China,

637
00:39:25,100 --> 00:39:27,020
I'll have them send it to the home.

638
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:29,140
Which home?

639
00:39:30,780 --> 00:39:31,540
Our home.

640
00:39:32,700 --> 00:39:33,340
Good boy.

641
00:39:39,260 --> 00:39:39,820
It's so sweet.

642
00:39:47,940 --> 00:39:48,580
Come on in.

643
00:39:52,140 --> 00:39:54,180
These are slippers for you.

644
00:40:07,620 --> 00:40:08,380
I've turned Xiaoyu's room

645
00:40:08,540 --> 00:40:09,980
into a study room.

646
00:40:12,180 --> 00:40:12,860
Okay.

647
00:40:14,340 --> 00:40:15,020
Where are you going?

648
00:40:16,140 --> 00:40:17,340
Didn't we agree

649
00:40:17,500 --> 00:40:19,540
I'd sleep in the study when I got back?

650
00:40:23,420 --> 00:40:24,860
Oh no, I forgot.

651
00:40:25,020 --> 00:40:26,620
I forgot to buy a bed for you.

652
00:40:32,050 --> 00:40:33,140
I'll sleep here then.

653
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:34,500
Okay.

654
00:40:34,860 --> 00:40:35,580
Then I'll get you

655
00:40:35,740 --> 00:40:36,820
a quilt and a pillow tonight.

656
00:40:37,340 --> 00:40:37,700
Okay.

657
00:40:37,820 --> 00:40:39,180
I'll put the stuff in first.

658
00:41:01,180 --> 00:41:02,780
Even if you want to sleep on the couch,

659
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:04,860
you can't just leave your things unpacked, right?

660
00:41:06,180 --> 00:41:07,620
I have too many things.

661
00:41:07,780 --> 00:41:09,260
I'll do the cleaning

662
00:41:09,420 --> 00:41:10,220
on my own

663
00:41:10,380 --> 00:41:11,500
after you're done unpacking.

664
00:41:11,660 --> 00:41:13,300
You won't be able to do it yourself.

665
00:41:13,620 --> 00:41:14,780
Only I know

666
00:41:14,900 --> 00:41:16,020
what goes where.

667
00:41:32,820 --> 00:41:33,780
That's all?

668
00:41:36,060 --> 00:41:37,620
I have some clothes on the way.

669
00:41:37,700 --> 00:41:38,460
They'll be here in a couple of days.

670
00:41:39,250 --> 00:41:40,820
Okay, I'll help you put the clothes

671
00:41:40,980 --> 00:41:41,940
in the closet first.

672
00:41:42,060 --> 00:41:42,570
I've made space

673
00:41:42,620 --> 00:41:43,300
on the left of the closet

674
00:41:43,460 --> 00:41:44,300
for your clothes.

675
00:41:44,460 --> 00:41:45,460
The right side is for me.

676
00:41:45,710 --> 00:41:47,180
You can put these books in the study.

677
00:41:47,300 --> 00:41:48,660
I've made space for your stuff too.

678
00:42:16,780 --> 00:42:18,060
You have more books coming?

679
00:42:18,500 --> 00:42:18,900
Yes.

680
00:42:20,340 --> 00:42:21,740
Are these shelves enough?

681
00:42:22,100 --> 00:42:23,260
If not, I'll make some more space for you.

682
00:42:26,580 --> 00:42:27,500
Should be enough.

683
00:42:30,740 --> 00:42:31,900
Do you usually

684
